Feasts are not everywhere.
In Hungary holidays are lawfully regulated, so the practice of redistributing working days around holidays has already established itself, but the next year will give us less such days.
Also in the EU and in the United States, something different is understood as "feasts".
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between state holidays and unemployment days.
Workless days are mostly church holidays, or are associated with significant historical events.
For example, we celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old and the first day of the new year are unemployment days - the latter alone so that the New Year celebrations can rest.
We have a total of 14 holidays throughout the year.
The national celebrations are the 15th March commemorating the Revolution of 1848 and the 23th October commemorating the Revolution of 1956.
On 20 August the state foundation is celebrated, on 1 May the work is celebrated, on 1 and 2 November we commemorate our dead.
In addition, there are two holidays each on Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas.
Since our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall into a weekend, the practice of "work day dismissal" has proven itself in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price of the prolonged weekends, however, is that we have to work very well on Saturday before it, or go to school.
When this day, which falls before or after the holidays, is intended to be finally processed, has been determined by the Minister of Labour in its own regulations for many years.
The legislation applies to all employers and recipients, public employees and public service officials equally.
Except only companies and institutions where the operation is continued without interruption, also on holidays.
Today, the working order is only somewhat disturbed by the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, the life in this country remains formal, as most take the time balance for the days between Christmas and New Year's Eve, or the vacation specially paid for it.
In the next year, more holidays will fall to the middle of the week or to the end of the week, so there will be fewer displays in the working days than this year.
The calendar is first put on the head around the day of work, so that people can stay at home equally for four days.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so Friday, May 2 can be a day of rest.
The second disclosure depends on the holiday on 23 October: on Saturday, 18 October, you will have to work out in advance on Friday, 24 October.
The end of the year, however, will be unrestless in the sign of holidays, after 24 December everything is and remains, even if New Year's Eve falls on a Wednesday.
