Which insurance is best for me?
The vehicle insurance that covers any possible damage caused by the driver involves a high cost, the amount of which, in turn, depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of drawing the driver’s license, family status, the type of the car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear what we have to do here.
A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is concluded in writing by means of an insurance agreement, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding amount of withdrawal in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver’s license, family status, type of the vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so in case of a higher accident risk, higher contributions will also be required.
For this reason, both over 25 years old and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups, thanks to their caution, have a lower rate of accidents.
The same applies to married persons, as they, according to statist values and therefore, according to the beliefs of companies, tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefit to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting the premium, the insurance companies need to take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also thoroughly study the situation to choose exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance so that we can make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
People under the age of 25 are confronted with numerous obstacles when choosing an affordable insurance, such as the low driving practice and the “young” driving license.
Even if it would be best to complete a full-cash insurance for an ideal insurance protection, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full casco with self-contribution, so the services of a full casco insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
“The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and according to the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher and lower than the amount to be paid,” explains Luis Noguera, the main representative of Spain at First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the advanced insurance that ensures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused on his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here is a advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it’s in your hand to reduce the insurance costs; so your credit rate increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the tariffs mentioned.
The amount of credit and penalties depends on the company and its revenue.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can be allowed to increase the bonus payments,” Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Therefore, it is most reasonable to choose a full cash insurance with self-contribution.
“Normally, young people can’t benefit from their past experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving,” explains the Spanish chairman of the European company, adding that the majority of the accidents occur in the second year of practice after the “beginner’s fear” was dissolved.
However, it is advisable for a married customer who does not have children to complete a full-cash insurance; of course only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows it.
On the side of the insurers, spouses with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and therefore their contributions are also low.
In this case, a full cash insurance with self-participation (with a amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In the case that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which is only used for the third year of the vehicle.
“They drive more relaxed in general and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment,” Luis Noguera notes.
For retirees, it is recommended to complete a full cash insurance with self-contribution (with a amount of €150) or an extended insurance that will only be used with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection that fits our personal situation.
