A new price dispute is ongoing between Ukraine and Russia, which increases the risk that Russian fuel exports to Western Europe will be affected.
Most of Russia’s natural gas exports to the European Union (EU) are directed by Ukraine and any dispute between the two nations is very closely monitored.
Kiev has warned that if Moscow increases the price it has to pay for natural gas, it will be charged by Russia with higher transit fees.
A previous conflict between the two countries last year reduced supplies to the EU countries.
