Manil's financial district was the main site of the attempted measurement of about 200 soldiers against Arroyo in 2003.
The rebellion failed after just 24 hours after the army refused to join.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven coup attempts against democratically elected governments in the Philippines.
United Internet becomes a major shareholder in Versatel
United Internet has secured a share of more than 20 percent in the telecommunications company Versatel.
The average price per share is 14.46 euros, the company on Wednesday evening.
It now holds 20.05 percent of the capital.
It was previously speculated about the acquisition.
The option is open to increasing the share of Versatel.
With the step we want to advance the consolidation of the German DSL market, United Internet said.
Earlier on Wednesday, suspicions had already arisen after the Berenberg Bank increased its share in the Düsseldorfer network operator by another 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
The money house holds the shares only for a third party, it was said in the financial market.
On the previous day, United Internet had already participated with 10 percent in the mobile company Trillisch.
As part of a capital increase, Drillisch has placed 17.4 million new shares worth 106.4 million euros.
5.15 million of these shares were purchased by United Internet for 31.4 million euros.
Furthermore, the companies began discussions on marketing cooperations for DSL and mobile communications products.
“We strengthen our partnership,” a United Internet spokesman explained.
The two companies have founded the Community company MSP to take over the competitor Freenet.
Currently, the two companies want to satisfy themselves with a share of more than 10 percent in Freenet and do not take advantage of their right to take over another 18.49 percent in Freenet, United Internet said on Thursday.
However, the two companies remained open to all options, especially to further increase their participation in Freenet AG.
The talks between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership were closed in mid-November.
The poker around Freenet, which lasts for months and is hard to understand, is part of the consolidation of the German telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million mobile contracts and 1.27 million DSL and full-connection customers.
The holding of United Internet and Drillisch so far held directly 6,01 percent of Freenet’s shares.
It is now agreed that Trillisch will bring about 4 percent more.
The right to buy the 18.49 percent from the investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
